.TH OPENTELEMETRY-INJECTOR 8 "@DATE@" "opentelemetry-injector @VERSION@" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
opentelemetry-injector \- LD_PRELOAD-based automatic instrumentation injector
.SH SYNOPSIS
The OpenTelemetry Injector is loaded automatically via
.B /etc/ld.so.preload
and requires no manual invocation.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B opentelemetry-injector
is an LD_PRELOAD-based mechanism that automatically injects OpenTelemetry
auto-instrumentation agents into processes at startup. It supports Java,
Node.js, .NET, and Python runtimes.
.PP
When a process starts, the injector library detects the runtime environment
and loads the appropriate OpenTelemetry agent to enable automatic telemetry
collection without code changes.
.SH FILES
.TP
.B /usr/lib/opentelemetry/injector/libotelinject.so
The injector shared library that is preloaded into processes.
.TP
.B /etc/opentelemetry/injector/injector.conf
Main configuration file specifying the default environment variables path
and documenting the conf.d drop-in mechanism.
.TP
.B /etc/opentelemetry/injector/default_env.conf
Default environment variables applied to all instrumented processes.
.TP
.B /etc/opentelemetry/injector/conf.d/
Directory for drop-in configuration files. Each language auto-instrumentation
package installs a file here to register its agent path. Files are read in
alphabetical order.
.TP
.B /etc/ld.so.preload
System file listing libraries to preload. The injector adds itself here
during installation.
.SH CONFIGURATION
The injector reads its main configuration from
.BR /etc/opentelemetry/injector/injector.conf .
Agent paths are registered via drop-in files in
.BR /etc/opentelemetry/injector/conf.d/ :
.TP
.B jvm_auto_instrumentation_agent_path
Path to the Java agent JAR file.
.TP
.B nodejs_auto_instrumentation_agent_path
Path to the Node.js agent entry point.
.TP
.B dotnet_auto_instrumentation_agent_path_prefix
Path prefix for the .NET agent (the injector resolves the glibc/
subdirectory beneath it).
.TP
.B python_auto_instrumentation_agent_path_prefix
Path prefix for the Python agent (the injector resolves the glibc/
subdirectory beneath it and prepends it to PYTHONPATH).
.SH ENVIRONMENT
The following environment variables can be used to control instrumentation:
.TP
.B OTEL_SERVICE_NAME
Set the service name for telemetry data.
.TP
.B OTEL_EXPORTER_OTLP_ENDPOINT
Set the OTLP exporter endpoint (e.g., http://localhost:4317).
.TP
.B OTEL_TRACES_EXPORTER
Set the traces exporter (e.g., otlp, console, none).
.TP
.B OTEL_METRICS_EXPORTER
Set the metrics exporter (e.g., otlp, console, none).
.TP
.B OTEL_LOGS_EXPORTER
Set the logs exporter (e.g., otlp, console, none).
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR ld.so (8),
.BR opentelemetry-java (8),
.BR opentelemetry-nodejs (8),
.BR opentelemetry-dotnet (8),
.BR opentelemetry-python (8)
